Tenno-no-Mori (天王の杜) is the former site of {{ill|Onji Shrine|ja|恩智神社|12=draft|12=draft}}. It was a shrine used during festivals, and although it is called a mori (forest), most of it is now an open space. The exact era and period of its construction are currently unknown <ref>http://www.yaomania.jp/data/InfoDetail.asp?id=1448</ref>
